<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="109" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="109">
<pageBreakToken pageId="2" pageNumber="109" start="start">Distribution</pageBreakToken>
and habitat.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="109">
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. F. Liu, S. R. Lan &amp; Y. C. Liang" authorityYear="2016" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Bulbophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bulbophyllum pingnanense" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pingnanense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Bulbophyllum pingnanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is so far only known within Pingnan, Fujian, China (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Distribution of Bulbophyllum pingnanense, Bulbophyllum brevipedunculatum and Bulbophyllum albociliatum." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.65.8254.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/94170" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">3</figureCitation>
). It is epiphytic on steep rock in the edge of evergreen coniferous and broad-leaved mixed forest, which is mainly composed of 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Castanopsis eyrei" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="eyrei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Castanopsis eyrei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Champ. ex Benth.) Hutch. (
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName class="Pinopsida" family="Taxodiaceae" genus="Cunninghamia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cunninghamia lanceolata" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Coniferophyta" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Cunninghamia lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Lamb.) Hook. (
<taxonomicName class="Pinopsida" family="Taxodiaceae" genus="Cunninghamia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Coniferophyta" rank="family">Taxodiaceae</taxonomicName>
). Other orchids, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schltr" authorityYear="1919" baseAuthorityName="Blume" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Amitostigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Amitostigma gracile" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gracile">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Amitostigma gracile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bl.) Schltr., 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pholidota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pholidota cantonensis" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cantonensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Pholidota cantonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Rolfe, 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Cymbidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbidium floribundum" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="floribundum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Cymbidium floribundum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lindl. and 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleione" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pleione formosana" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="formosana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Pleione formosana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hayata, were found growing nearby this new species.
</paragraph>
